PN,44609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1776258665
OL,3,C'Likely' Noah Donohoe was alive when
OL,4,Che entered storm drain, inquest told
OL,6,F"I think it is very likely that the
OL,7,Fboy drowned at or about this time and
OL,8,Flocation. It is possible, but
OL,9,Funlikely, that the body was moved a
OL,10,Fshort distance upstream or downstream
OL,11,Ffrom the point at which it was
OL,12,Frecovered by floating."
OL,14,FProf Roberts also found that it is
OL,15,Fprobable that Noah drowned in seawater
OL,16,Fmixed with fresh water during the
OL,17,Fincoming tide while confused.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/12
